why did i buy this ? what 's worse than a bad cd ? `` the burdens of being upright . '' i do n't even know where to start . i bought it because i really liked the first song `` mother mother '' ( which is the only reason why tracy bonham even gets 2 stars from me ) ... and i was completely disappointed with the rest of the album . the songs are n't interesting and the whole thing all in all is just simply not worth the money . unless its used and only costs like , two bucks . actually , when i went to to trade it in at the record store , they only offered me 25 cents for it because they have so many copies of it and nobody wants them . and i took the quarter ! if you like grunge music , there 's a chance that you might like this , but you most likely still wo n't